description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a cheerful and motivated person to join our busy team in the Corneo Plastic Unit at the Queen Victoria Hospital East Grinstead. The successful candidate will work alongside the nursing and medical team in the department with a variety of Opthalmic clinics and diagnostics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will be empathetic, caring and compassionate. You will be reliable, self motivated and able to work as a member of the team assisting in the daily running of the clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Orientation, training and supervision will be provided. Good IT skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Queen Victoria Hospital offers developmental oppurtunities for Health Care Assistants. You will be enrolled on the Care Certificate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lynn Martin&lt;br /&gt;Matron Corneo Plastic Unit&lt;br /&gt;lynn.martin3@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;01342 414569&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mimi Dizon, Deputy Matron 01342 414166&lt;/p&gt;
